{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69ee-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1804"},"text":"§ 1804.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Inland and intracoastal waterways of the United States","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s4042"},"text":"section 4042 of title 26","children":[],"tail":" (relating to tax on fuel used in commercial transportation on inland waterways) and for purposes of section 1802 "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002083"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002083"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of this title, the following inland and intracoastal waterways of the United States are described in this section:"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69ef-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Alabama-Coosa Rivers: From junction with the Tombigbee River at river mile (hereinafter referred to as RM) 0 to junction with Coosa River at RM 314.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69f0-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Allegheny River: From confluence with the Monongahela River to form the Ohio River at RM 0 to the head of the existing project at East Brady, Pennsylvania, RM 72.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69f1-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Apalachicola-Chattahoochee and Flint Rivers: Apalachicola River from mouth at Apalachicola Bay (intersection with the Gulf Intracoastal Waterway) RM 0 to junction with Chattachoochee ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002084"},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002084"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be “Chattahoochee”."}],"tail":" and Flint Rivers at RM 107.8. Chattachoochee "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002084"},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":" River from junction with Apalachicola and Flint Rivers at RM 0 to Columbus, Georgia, at RM 155 and Flint River, from junction with Apalachicola and Chattahoochee Rivers at RM 0 to Bainbridge, Georgia, at RM 28."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69f2-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Arkansas River (McClellan-Kerr Arkansas River Navigation System): From junction with Mississippi River at RM 0 to port of Catoosa, Oklahoma, at RM 448.2.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69f3-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Atchafalaya River: From RM 0 at its intersection with the Gulf Intracoastal Waterway at Morgan City, Louisiana, upstream to junction with Red River at RM 116.8.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69f4-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Atlantic Intracoastal Waterway: Two inland water routes approximately paralleling the Atlantic coast between Norfolk, Virginia, and Miami, Florida, for 1,192 miles via both the Albermarle ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002085"},"text":"3","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002085"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"3","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be “Albemarle”."}],"tail":" and Chesapeake Canal and Great Dismal Swamp Canal routes."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69f5-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Black Warrior-Tombigbee-Mobile Rivers: Black Warrior River System from RM 2.9, Mobile River (at Chickasaw Creek) to confluence with Tombigbee River at RM 45. Tombigbee River (to Demopolis at RM 215.4) to port of Birmingham, RM’s 374–411 and upstream to head of navigation on Mulberry Fork (RM 429.6), Locust Fork (RM 407.8), and Sipsey Fork (RM 430.4).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69f6-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Columbia River (Columbia-Snake Rivers Inland Waterways): From The Dalles at RM 191.5 to Pasco, Washington (McNary Pool), at RM 330, Snake River from RM 0 at the mouth to RM 231.5 at Johnson Bar Landing, Idaho.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69f7-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9"},"text":"(9)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Cumberland River: Junction with Ohio River at RM 0 to head of navigation, upstream to Carthage, Tennessee, at RM 313.5.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69f8-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/10"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10"},"text":"(10)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Green and Barren Rivers: Green River from junction with the Ohio River at RM 0 to head of navigation at RM 149.1.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69f9-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/11"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"11"},"text":"(11)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Gulf Intracoastal Waterway: From St. Mark’s River, Florida, to Brownsville, Texas, 1,134.5 miles.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69fa-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/12"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"12"},"text":"(12)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Illinois Waterway (Calumet-Sag Channel): From the junction of the Illinois River with the Mississippi River RM 0 to Chicago Harbor at Lake Michigan, approximately RM 350.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69fb-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/13"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"13"},"text":"(13)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Kanawha River: From junction with Ohio River at RM 0 to RM 90.6 at Deepwater, West Virginia.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69fc-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/14"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"14"},"text":"(14)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Kaskaskia River: From junction with the Mississippi River at RM 0 to RM 36.2 at Fayetteville, Illinois.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69fd-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/15"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"15"},"text":"(15)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Kentucky River: From junction with Ohio River at RM 0 to confluence of Middle and North Forks at RM 258.6.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69fe-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/16"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"16"},"text":"(16)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Lower Mississippi River: From Baton Rouge, Louisiana, RM 233.9 to Cairo, Illinois, RM 953.8.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b69ff-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/17"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"17"},"text":"(17)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Upper Mississippi River: From Cairo, Illinois, RM 953.8 to Minneapolis, Minnesota, RM 1,811.4.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b6a00-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/18"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"18"},"text":"(18)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Missouri River: From junction with Mississippi River at RM 0 to Sioux City, Iowa, at RM 734.8.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b6a01-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/19"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"19"},"text":"(19)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Monongahela River: From junction with Allegheny River to form the Ohio River at RM 0 to junction of the Tygart and West Fork Rivers, Fairmont, West Virginia, at RM 128.7.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b6a02-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/20"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"20"},"text":"(20)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Ohio River: From junction with the Mississippi River at RM 0 to junction of the Allegheny and Monongahela Rivers at Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, at RM 981.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b6a03-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/21"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"21"},"text":"(21)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Ouachita-Black Rivers: From the mouth of the Black River at its junction with the Red River at RM 0 to RM 351 at Camden, Arkansas.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b6a04-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/22"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"22"},"text":"(22)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Pearl River: From junction of West Pearl River with the Rigolets at RM 0 to Bogalusa, Louisiana, RM 58.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b6a05-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/23"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"23"},"text":"(23)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Red River: From RM 0 to the mouth of Cypress Bayou at RM 236.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b6a06-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/24"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"24"},"text":"(24)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Tennessee River: From junction with Ohio River at RM 0 to confluence with Holstein and French Rivers at RM 652.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b6a07-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/25"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"25"},"text":"(25)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" White River: From RM 9.8 to RM 255 at Newport, Arkansas.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b6a08-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/26"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"26"},"text":"(26)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Willamette River: From RM 21 upstream of Portland, Oregon, to Harrisburg, Oregon, at RM 194.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b6a09-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1804/27"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"27"},"text":"(27)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Tennessee-Tombigbee Waterway: From its confluence with the Tennessee River to the Warrior River at Demopolis, Alabama.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6c1b6a0a-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/502/tII/s206"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–502, title II, § 206","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/1700"},"text":"92 Stat. 1700","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib